CMS Missing Digital Contact Information API

Source: vignettes/articles/cms-miss-contact-info.Rmd
cms-miss-contact-info.Rmd
library(provider)


Information on Providers That are Missing Digital Contact Information in the NPPES System.


Digital contact information, also known as Endpoints, provides a secure way for health care entities to send authenticated, encrypted health information to trusted recipients over the internet. Health care organizations seeking to engage in electronic health information exchange need accurate information about the electronic addresses (for example, Direct address, FHIR server URL, query endpoint, or other digital contact information) of potential exchange partners to facilitate this information exchange.


missing_information() != nppes_npi()

A provider that appears in the search results of the Missing Information API has no Endpoints entered into the NPPES NPI Registry.

missing_information(npi = 1144224569)
#> Error in loadNamespace(x): there is no package called 'kableExtra'
nppes_npi(npi = 1144224569)
#> Error in loadNamespace(x): there is no package called 'kableExtra'



nppes_npi() != missing_information()

A provider with Endpoint information in the NPPES will not appear in the Missing Information search results.

nppes_npi(npi = 1144224569)
#> Error in loadNamespace(x): there is no package called 'kableExtra'
missing_information(npi = 1003000423)
#> Error in loadNamespace(x): there is no package called 'kableExtra'


API Data Dictionary

Variable Term Definition

npi

 NPI The provider's 10-digit National Provider Identifier.

provider_name

 Provider Name Name of the provider. It consists of the legal last name followed by the first name, separated by a comma.
